issue.title: [✨Feature] 부스 & 메뉴 API : 부스 정보 & 부스 메뉴 조회 기능

type.name: Feature
type.description: A request, idea, or new functionality

issue.body:
## 어떤 기능을 제안하나요?

GET /api/festival/booth
-> 부스를 전체를 조회하는 API입니다.
-> 메뉴를 제외한 정보가 조회됩니다.

GET /api/festival/booth/{name}
-> 부스 이름으로 조회하는 API입니다.
-> 부스 이름과 일치하는 모든 정보가 조회됩니다.

GET /api/festival/booths/{boothName}/menus
-> 부스 이름으로 그 부스의 전체 메뉴가 조회됩니다.

브랜치 명 feat/booth-menu-api

---

## 설명

1. 개요

>부스 목록 조회(페이징) -> 공연 목록을 페이지 단위로 조회. 정렬과 기본/최대 페이지 크기 지원.

2) 요청 규격 (쿼리 파라미터)

이름 | 타입 | 필수 | 기본값 | 예시 | 설명 | 제약
-- | -- | -- | -- | -- | -- | --
page | integer | 선택 | 0 | 0 | 0부터 시작하는 페이지 번호 | 0 ≤ page
size | integer | 선택 | 10 | 20 | 한 페이지에 조회할 데이터 개수 | 1 ≤ size ≤ 50
sort | string | 선택 | date,desc | title,asc / date,desc | 정렬 기준 필드와 방향 | 허용 필드: date, title, createdAt방향: asc(오름차순), desc(내림차순)


## ✅ 체크리스트
- [X] 브랜치 컨벤션을 지키세요

---

## 📎 Response Body

부스 전체 목록 조회 (페이징)
```json
{
  "code": "SUCCESS",
  "message": "요청이 성공했습니다.",
  "data": {
    "boothMapImg": "https://example.com/map.jpg", // 부스 지도 이미지 URL
    "meta": {
      "page": 1,                 // 현재 페이지 번호
      "pageSize": 10,             // 한 페이지당 아이템 개수
      "total": 123,               // 전체 데이터 개수
      "totalPages": 13,           // 전체 페이지 수
      "hasPrev": false,           // 이전 페이지 존재 여부
      "hasNext": true,            // 다음 페이지 존재 여부
      "sort": "-startTime,name",  // 정렬 기준 (-: 내림차순, ,로 다중 필드 가능)
      "filters": {                // 현재 적용된 검색/필터 조건
        "subject_type": null,     // 부스 주제 유형 필터(예: 학과, 동아리)
        "goods_type": null        // 판매/제공 유형 필터(예: 물품, 체험)
      }
    },
    "booth": [
      {
        "booth_id": 1,
        "name": "게임 부스",
        "type": "학과",
        "department": "컴퓨터공학과",
        "startTime": "09:00",
        "endTime": "18:00",
        "goods_type": "체험",
        "boothImg": "https://example.com/1.jpg"
      },
      {
        "booth_id": 2,
        "name": "닭꼬치 푸드트럭",
        "type": "푸드트럭",
        "department": "푸드트럭",
        "startTime": "09:00",
        "endTime": "17:00",
        "goods_type": "물품",
        "boothImg": "https://example.com/2.jpg"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

부스 이름으로 조회 후 이름에 해당하는 정보 조회
```json
{
  "code": "SUCCESS",
  "message": "요청이 성공했습니다.",
  "data": {
    "booth_id": 2,
    "name": "닭꼬치 푸드트럭",
    "type": "푸드트럭",
    "department": "푸드트럭",
    "startTime": "09:00",
    "endTime": "17:00",
    "introduction": "저희는 경영 학생들이 준비한 푸드트럭입니다.",
    "goods_type": "물품",
    "menu": "닭꼬치, 타코야끼",
    "boothLocation": "정문 앞 광장"
  }
}
```

부스 이름에 해당하는 메뉴 전체 조회 (페이징x)

  "code": "SUCCESS",

      {

pull_request.body: ## 개요 - 부스 목록 조회 API 구현 - 부스 세부 목록 조회 API 구현 - 부스 조회시 메뉴 목록도 조회 구현 - close #35 ## 설명 - `GET` `http://localhost:8080/api/festival/booth` : 모든 부스 조회 (페이징 단위) - `GET` `http://localhost:8080/api/festival/booth/{boothName}` : 부스 이름으로 공연 정보 조회 - `GET` `http://localhost:8080/api/festival/{boothName}/menus` : 부스 이름을 요청하면 메뉴목록 정보 제공 - BoothMenuDevSeeder : 후에 데이터 삽입시 사용할 코드파일 ## API요청 메시지 ### 성공 ### 실패 - 부스는 있는데 메뉴가 없으면 메뉴는 빈 리스트를 반환함 ### 📌 수정 및 변경(코드) - [x] 버그 수정 - [x] 코드 리팩토링 ### 📌 구조 변경 - [x] 파일 혹은 폴더명 수정 - [x] 파일 혹은 폴더 삭제 ### 📌 문서 작성 및 수정 - [x] 문서 수정 : 마지막 커밋 메시지에 refactor: 명시x -> chore로 빈 커밋내용 올림 --- ## 🔥 PR Checklist **리뷰어**를 위해, PR이 다음 요구 사항을 충족하는지 확인하세요. - [x] 리뷰어 설정을 했나요? - [x] 커밋 메시지, 코드 컨벤션에 맞게 작성했나요? - [x] 변경 사항에 대한 테스트를 했습니다. - [x] 🔥 병합 위치가 올바른 브랜치인지 확인하셨나요? - [x] 진짜 했나요?

issue.title: Chell: No audio after kernel update (Arch)
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
After upgrading my kernel from 6.15.x to 6.16.x, I no longer have working audio and only have a Dummy Output in PulseAudio.

It seems to stem from something being wrong with at least one of the ucm2 configs as the first line I get when the script calls alsactl init is this:

"alsa-lib main.c:1554:(snd_use_case_mgr_open) error: failed to import hw:0 use case configuration -2"

Under /usr/share/alsa/ucm2 I've tried removing stuff that would have come from the script (eg. anything from /tmp/alsa-ucm-conf-cros) before running the script again to no avail but I could well have missed something as I'm not very well versed in alsa configuration.

**Distro name and version**
Arch Linux

**Boardname**
Chell

**Logs**

[debug-logs-Chell-2025-08-16_12h33m.tar.gz](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21815483/debug-logs-Chell-2025-08-16_12h33m.tar.gz)

issue.title: Using GAS on 32bit mingw builds fails to link
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When using GAS to build a 32bit Loader for Windows, it fails at link-time because the GAS assembly does not properly decorate the functions for stdcall like the masm one does:

```
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(dev_ext_trampoline.c.obj):dev_ext_trampoline.c:(.rdata+0x0): undefined reference to `vkdev_ext0@4'
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(dev_ext_trampoline.c.obj):dev_ext_trampoline.c:(.rdata+0x4): undefined reference to `vkdev_ext1@4'
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(dev_ext_trampoline.c.obj):dev_ext_trampoline.c:(.rdata+0x8): undefined reference to `vkdev_ext2@4'
....
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(phys_dev_ext.c.obj):phys_dev_ext.c:(.rdata+0x0): undefined reference to `vkPhysDevExtTermin0@4'
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(phys_dev_ext.c.obj):phys_dev_ext.c:(.rdata+0x4): undefined reference to `vkPhysDevExtTermin1@4'
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(phys_dev_ext.c.obj):phys_dev_ext.c:(.rdata+0x8): undefined reference to `vkPhysDevExtTermin2@4'
...
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(phys_dev_ext.c.obj):phys_dev_ext.c:(.rdata+0x400): undefined reference to `vkPhysDevExtTramp0@4'
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(phys_dev_ext.c.obj):phys_dev_ext.c:(.rdata+0x404): undefined reference to `vkPhysDevExtTramp1@4'
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(phys_dev_ext.c.obj):phys_dev_ext.c:(.rdata+0x408): undefined reference to `vkPhysDevExtTramp2@4'
...
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(unknown_ext_chain_gas_x86.S.obj):fake:(.text+0x12ba): undefined reference to `loader_log_asm_function_not_supported'
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(unknown_ext_chain_gas_x86.S.obj):fake:(.text+0x12f4): undefined reference to `loader_log_asm_function_not_supported'
/opt/ct-ng/lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/15.1.0/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld: CMakeFiles/vulkan.dir/objects.a(unknown_ext_chain_gas_x86.S.obj):fake:(.text+0x132e): undefined reference to `loader_log_asm_function_not_supported'
...
```

**Environment (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: Cross-Compiling from Linux to Win32
 - Bitdepth: 32bit
 - GPU: any
 - Graphics Driver: any
 - SDK or header version if building from repo: v1.4.325
 - Enabled layers: none

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
Build the loader for win32 using mingw and gas.

**VK_LOADER_DEBUG output**
Doesn't get this far.

**Additional context**
The masm assembly has its functions properly decorated when in 32bit mode, most of them with @4 and the leading underscore.
The GAS assembly does not do this for 32bit. Which is fine on 64bit Windows, but not for 32bit.

Either GAS support needs to be just plain disabled for Windows 32bit builds, or the assembly needs to properly decorate the functions for stdcall (and actually do stdcall calling convention stuff, I don't understand the assembly well enough to see if it does that, or has to do anything for that)

issue.title: Pressable elements not working in native-stack on Android devices with new architecture

labels.name: Platform: Android
labels.description: This issue is specific to Android

labels.name: Repro provided
labels.description: A reproduction with a snack or repo is provided

labels.name: NewArch
labels.description: Issues related only to new architecture

issue.body:
### Description

When using Android devices (iOS and Android emulator is fine) you cannot use onPress in the header bar. onPressIn and onPress out does work. This was tested mostly with Samsung devices.
This only happens with native-stack / Expo Router.

Please have a look here: 
https://github.com/expo/expo/issues/30032
https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation/issues/12039
https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/44643

### Steps to reproduce

1. Use react navigation native-stack with new arch enabled on RN 0.74
2. Go to a stack screen and try to press elements with onPress
3. onPress elements wont work. onPressIn and onPressOut does

### Snack or a link to a repository

https://github.com/DrZoidberg09/RN-Android-Touch-Issue/

For comparison a repo with bare RN, one with Expo and react navigation stack and one with Expo router / native-stack

### Screens version

3.32.0

### React Native version

0.74

### Platforms

Android

### JavaScript runtime

Hermes

### Workflow

None

### Architecture

Fabric (New Architecture)

### Build type

None

### Device

None

### Device model

Samsung S23, Samsung S8+

### Acknowledgements

Yes

# Transforming Code Reviews with AI

## Features

**Automated Reviews**: Continuous reviews of the pull requests including incremental commits. 

**Summarization**: Generates high-level summary and a technical walkthrough of the PR changes. 

**Line-by-line review**: Provides line-by-line suggestions committable with one click.

**Codebase verification**:  Verifies the impact on the overall codebase and identifies missing changes.

**Insights into your code**:  Ask any questions on your codebase within the pull request 

**Chat about your code** : Chat with the bot around your code. The more you chat, the smarter it gets.

**Issue Validation**:  Validates the PR against the linked issues and identifies other related issues
